==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|hevy|lang=enm}}, {{term|heviȝ|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|hefig|hefiġ|lang=ang}}, {{term|hefeg|hefeġ|lang=ang}}, {{term|hæfig|hæfiġ|heavy; important, grave, severe, serious; oppressive, grievous; slow, dull|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|habīgaz||heavy, hefty, weighty|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|keh₂p-||to take, grasp, hold|lang=ine-pro}}, equivalent to {{suffix|heave|y}}. Cognate with {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|hevy|lang=sco}}, {{term|havy|lang=sco}}, {{term|heavy||heavy|lang=sco}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|hevig||violent, severe, intense, acute|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|gml|-}} {{term|hevich|hēvich|violent, fierce, intense|lang=gml}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|hebig|lang=de}} (cf. {{term|heftig||fierce, severe, intense, violent, heavy|lang=de}}), {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|höfugur||heavy, weighty, important|lang=is}}, {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|capax|capāx|large, wide, roomy, spacious, capacious, capable, apt|lang=la}}.

